title.narrative: TPC: INL/AP Foreign Affairs Program Assistant

description.narrative: BPA call modification to fully fund Option Year Two (02) in the amount of $84,035.20 for the services of a Foreign Affairs Program Assistant for INL/AP located in Washington, D.C.. BPA Call modification to de-obligate funding in the amount of $194.28 from a canceling year appropriation, which will no longer be available for expenditure effective 01-OCT-2020, for the services of a Foreign Affairs Program Assistant for INL/AP located in Information Redacted , D.C.. BPA Call modification to de-obligate funding in the amount of $194.28 from a canceling year appropriation, which will no longer be available for expenditure effective 01-OCT-2020, for the services of a Foreign Affairs Program Assistant for INL/AP located in Washington, D.C.. TPC: INL/AP Foreign Affairs Program Assistant Information Redacted [Covers individual experts and consultants possessing special, current knowledge, and skill which may be combined with extensive operational experience. They provide information, opinions, advice, or recommendations that enhance understanding of complex issues or improve the quality and timeliness of policy development and decision-making. Contract experts and consultants do not supervise or perform operating functions nor do they receive direct supervision. Contract experts and consultants serving on advisory committees are to be assigned to subobject code 2505.]. BPA Call modification to increase Supplemental Hours, which are authorized, in the amount of $1,327.60 for the services of a Foreign Affairs Program Assistant for INL/AP located in Washington, D.C.
